♪Just right now♪

16
00:01:21,690 --> 00:01:24,512
♪Time will speak your truth aloud♪

17
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:26,848
♪No time gap between tomorrow and I♪

18
00:01:26,848 --> 00:01:29,010
♪Tears are blossoming♪

19
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:31,110
♪The path of hope never divides♪

20
00:01:31,110 --> 00:01:33,280
♪Waiting for sunlight's embrace♪

21
00:01:36,570 --> 00:01:38,240
♪Just right now♪

22
00:01:38,670 --> 00:01:40,030
♪Take the field immediately♪

23
00:01:40,798 --> 00:01:44,015
=All Rise=

24
00:01:45,084 --> 00:01:47,784
=Episode 20=

25
00:01:49,019 --> 00:01:50,248
(Talent Hunt Program Day 66)

26
00:01:50,248 --> 00:01:52,168
(Guo Xiaoyu 3, Yan Fei 2)

27
00:01:52,168 --> 00:01:53,800
(Ren Jiatong 1, Jiang Chen 1)

28
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:57,281
I didn't edit the presentation.
Ms. Bai did it.

29
00:01:58,720 --> 00:01:59,320
Ms. Bai?

30
00:02:01,841 --> 00:02:03,080
When you sent it to me,

31
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:03,841
I was asleep.

32
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:07,001
I sent it at 3 AM.

33
00:02:07,561 --> 00:02:08,841
We must be here by 7 AM.

34
00:02:09,521 --> 00:02:10,561
Didn't Ms. Bai sleep?

35
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:13,760
She must be exhausted.
She spent all day in court.

36
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,336
Now, she has to handle the family.

37
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,760
But Ms. Bai didn't scold me once today.

38
00:02:21,841 --> 00:02:23,121
She appreciated my hard work.

39
00:02:23,841 --> 00:02:25,720
Doesn't it feel worse
if she doesn't scold you?

40
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,480
It means she is teaching you.

41
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:31,961
You'll remember this moment.

42
00:02:32,283 --> 00:02:32,961
(Serving the People with Fair Justice)

43
00:02:32,961 --> 00:02:34,361
Many people say she's strict.

44
00:02:35,001 --> 00:02:37,081
Actually, she just takes work seriously,

45
00:02:37,561 --> 00:02:38,361
not against anyone.

46
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,801
Work is the most important thing to her.

47
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:43,160
No matter how tired,
she never slacks off.

48
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:47,521
If I'd been more diligent,

49
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:49,480
Ms. Bai could get two hours of sleep.

50
00:02:49,681 --> 00:02:50,561
Stop feeling guilty.

51
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:53,290
You're a newcomer.
It's normal to be inexperienced.

52
00:02:53,290 --> 00:02:57,801
If anyone's to blame, it should be me.
I should have edited it.

53
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,360
Ms. Bai's child had a fever last night.

54
00:03:00,801 --> 00:03:01,561
Remember when she

55
00:03:01,561 --> 00:03:02,801
took a long call last night?

56
00:03:03,521 --> 00:03:07,040
It was from the nanny.
She must've been worried.

57
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,584
And she stayed up late working.

58
00:03:19,516 --> 00:03:20,936
(Zhou Nian)

59
00:03:20,956 --> 00:03:22,024
(Experience Sharing)

60
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,001
Yan Fei.

61
00:03:39,801 --> 00:03:41,401
Are you working overtime?

62
00:03:42,961 --> 00:03:44,561
Any problem with me working overtime?

63
00:03:46,121 --> 00:03:48,320
I've never seen you
at the firm this late.

64
00:03:49,801 --> 00:03:51,200
Am I really that lazy?

65
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:54,160
Why are you here at this hour?

66
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:55,841
Working overtime for Mr. Song?

67
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,640
When is your project wrapping up?

68
00:03:59,121 --> 00:04:00,440
I'm just wrapping things up now.

69
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:02,920
I'll rejoin Ms. Bai's team next week.
How about you?

70
00:04:03,081 --> 00:04:03,600
Any plans?

71
00:04:05,281 --> 00:04:05,896
Me?

72
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,841
I used to oppose my brother.

73
00:04:12,241 --> 00:04:13,681
He assigned me to Mr. Zhuang's team.

74
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:15,681
I wanted to join Mr. Song's team.

75
00:04:16,121 --> 00:04:17,601
But he suddenly changed his attitude.

76
00:04:17,601 --> 00:04:18,801
No clue what got into him.

77
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,064
He supports me in joining
Mr. Song's team.

78
00:04:21,721 --> 00:04:23,921
But I'm also interested

79
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,200
in Ms. Bai's case.

80
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:28,280
Someone is tutoring you. Who's so nice?

81
00:04:31,001 --> 00:04:31,560
Look.

82
00:04:32,161 --> 00:04:32,760
Shooting stars.

83
00:04:34,721 --> 00:04:36,161
Miss Yan,

84
00:04:36,161 --> 00:04:38,320
your skills of changing
the topic are terrible.

85
00:04:40,801 --> 00:04:42,601
I knew you are working overtime

86
00:04:42,601 --> 00:04:44,960
for the sake of someone.

87
00:04:45,241 --> 00:04:45,801
Let's talk.

88
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:47,624
Sure.

89
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:48,840
Let's talk.

90
00:04:49,681 --> 00:04:51,041
We can talk

91
00:04:51,121 --> 00:04:53,561
about Ren Jiatong
getting a cold last time.

92
00:04:55,161 --> 00:04:56,921
Oh, it's a meteor shower.

93
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,320
So many shooting stars.

94
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,241
Isn't Mr. Song looking for you?

95
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,640
He had important things to do and left.

96
00:05:13,721 --> 00:05:15,041
I'm with Niuniu at the hospital.

97
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:15,921
Don't worry.

98
00:05:16,681 --> 00:05:17,561
Thank you for this.

99
00:05:17,561 --> 00:05:19,161
The nanny sprained her ankle.

100
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:20,601
I...

101
00:05:20,601 --> 00:05:22,320
Don't mention it.

102
00:05:23,241 --> 00:05:25,400
I'm happy that you
thought of me first when you

103
00:05:25,801 --> 00:05:26,561
needed help.

104
00:05:28,121 --> 00:05:28,776
Alright.

105
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,041
I'll treat you to dinner when I'm back.

106
00:05:31,336 --> 00:05:31,921
Okay.

107
00:05:32,241 --> 00:05:32,880
I'm hanging up.

108
00:05:33,241 --> 00:05:35,001
I'm with Niuniu. Focus on your work.

109
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,200
Come back early.

110
00:05:43,481 --> 00:05:44,040
Ms. Bai.

111
00:05:44,801 --> 00:05:46,152
It's cold. Don't catch a chill.

112
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,200
Mr. Song specifically asked me

113
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:50,481
to bring you a scarf
since your neck is bothering you.

114
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:51,912
Okay.

115
00:05:52,681 --> 00:05:53,384
Thank you.

116
00:05:54,481 --> 00:05:55,176
Ms. Bai.

117
00:05:56,361 --> 00:05:57,361
I apologize to you.

118
00:05:58,840 --> 00:05:59,481
For what?

119
00:06:02,241 --> 00:06:02,960
Rest assured,

120
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:04,921
I'll stay up all night if needed.

121
00:06:04,921 --> 00:06:06,640
What happened last night
won't happen again.

122
00:06:11,721 --> 00:06:13,241
You haven't fully recovered yet.

123
00:06:13,241 --> 00:06:14,200
Don't stay up late.

124
00:06:15,161 --> 00:06:16,840
Health is part of your competitive edge.

125
00:06:18,001 --> 00:06:18,640
Moreover,

126
00:06:18,801 --> 00:06:20,640
if your mother knows you're sick,

127
00:06:21,161 --> 00:06:22,001
she will worry.

128
00:06:22,001 --> 00:06:23,041
Unable to help at all,

129
00:06:23,241 --> 00:06:24,320
she'd feel even worse.

130
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,161
Thank you, Ms. Bai.

131
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:31,721
Don't worry.

132
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,481
Niuniu will definitely recover soon.

133
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,280
This time,

134
00:06:37,801 --> 00:06:38,801
we're sure to win.

135
00:06:41,851 --> 00:06:44,584
(Jiang Chen: Voice message)

136
00:06:44,668 --> 00:06:46,632
(Jiang Chen: Two voice messages)

137
00:07:00,481 --> 00:07:02,280
When a person always delays

138
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:04,760
in replying to you, does it mean
this person doesn't like you?

139
00:07:05,121 --> 00:07:05,640
Not really.

140
00:07:06,241 --> 00:07:07,280
Maybe he did reply,

141
00:07:07,681 --> 00:07:09,121
but his phone swallowed it.

142
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:13,840
Something is going on?

143
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,840
Let me help you analyze this.

144
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,001
Which guy is it?

145
00:07:19,561 --> 00:07:20,681
I actually asked him

146
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,200
if he likes me.

147
00:07:22,601 --> 00:07:23,280
What did he say?

148
00:07:24,601 --> 00:07:26,481
He said he does like me,

149
00:07:27,001 --> 00:07:27,880
but it's the kind

150
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,880
of care and affection
toward a younger sibling.

151
00:07:31,361 --> 00:07:32,840
Not romantic feelings at all.

152
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,320
He had a girlfriend before,

153
00:07:35,921 --> 00:07:37,601
and she must be quite different from me.

154
00:07:38,161 --> 00:07:38,960
She is really nice

155
00:07:39,001 --> 00:07:40,161
and quite good-looking.

156
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,768
They had been together for years.

157
00:07:41,921 --> 00:07:43,840
Though they're broken up now...

158
00:07:45,721 --> 00:07:46,801
What am I even saying?

159
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,681
Anyway, I regret it now.

160
00:07:49,681 --> 00:07:50,520
I shouldn't ask him.

161
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,161
You like him.

162
00:07:52,241 --> 00:07:53,601
I don't know whether he likes you.

163
00:07:53,721 --> 00:07:54,840
But you definitely like him.

164
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,520
Impossible.

165
00:07:57,801 --> 00:07:59,601
Answering so quickly is suspicious.

166
00:07:59,921 --> 00:08:01,481
I wouldn't fall for a lawyer.

167
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:02,681
A male lawyer.

168
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,161
Miss Yan.

169
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,041
Anyway, it's someone I shouldn't like.

170
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,681
Now I've confessed

171
00:08:10,681 --> 00:08:11,760
and embarrassed myself.

172
00:08:12,481 --> 00:08:13,481
Jiang Chen, listen,

173
00:08:13,481 --> 00:08:14,440
if you spill this,

174
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,561
I'll hit you.

175
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,361
Smile.

176
00:08:20,001 --> 00:08:21,041
Why? That's so cheesy.

177
00:08:21,241 --> 00:08:22,361
I'll send you this photo.

178
00:08:22,681 --> 00:08:23,481
Then,

179
00:08:23,601 --> 00:08:25,280
you'll post it on Moments later.

180
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:26,760
Any caption is okay.

181
00:08:26,801 --> 00:08:28,280
Make sure only he can see it.

182
00:08:28,561 --> 00:08:29,121
I believe

183
00:08:29,121 --> 00:08:30,880
that if this guy truly
has feelings for you

184
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:31,960
or likes you,

185
00:08:32,241 --> 00:08:33,201
he will respond.

186
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:35,400
Really?

187
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:36,441
Of course.

188
00:08:36,721 --> 00:08:37,680
Like cross-examination.

189
00:08:38,241 --> 00:08:40,121
What're you thinking?
Have you thought about it?

190
00:08:40,121 --> 00:08:41,961
If not, what are you dwelling on?

191
00:08:42,121 --> 00:08:43,121
But if you have,

192
00:08:43,201 --> 00:08:44,520
delete that post.

193
00:08:47,721 --> 00:08:48,392
Okay.

194
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,216
I'm posting it.

195
00:09:14,139 --> 00:09:16,456
(Me in his eyes)

196
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,361
The takeout.

197
00:09:52,841 --> 00:09:53,441
Thanks.

198
00:10:06,441 --> 00:10:07,080
Got it.

199
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:08,040
I see.

200
00:10:11,321 --> 00:10:12,841
Ms. Bai, how's Niuniu doing?

201
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:16,424
- Her fever has gone down.
- That's a relief.

202
00:10:17,361 --> 00:10:18,441
We have a court tomorrow,

203
00:10:18,441 --> 00:10:20,441
so no one should stay up late tonight.

204
00:10:20,841 --> 00:10:22,640
Zhou Nian, I reviewed your part.

205
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:23,520
No issues there.

206
00:10:23,841 --> 00:10:24,800
Head back and sleep.

207
00:10:25,241 --> 00:10:27,121
I'll check Ren Jiatong's part later.

208
00:10:27,721 --> 00:10:28,296
Alright.

209
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:29,361
Sure.

210
00:10:29,361 --> 00:10:30,800
Ms. Bai, rest early once you finish.

211
00:10:34,721 --> 00:10:35,880
Mr. Zhou, aren't you eating?

212
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:36,808
I won't.

213
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,664
I'm going back.
I'm tired and I will sleep.

214
00:10:57,441 --> 00:10:58,001
Ms. Bai,

215
00:10:58,560 --> 00:10:59,481
this part...

216
00:10:59,481 --> 00:11:00,361
Take a break.

217
00:11:00,361 --> 00:11:01,880
Eat something right now.

218
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:13,448
What's wrong?

219
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:16,241
Promise you won't get mad.

220
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,280
These high-calorie snacks

221
00:11:21,441 --> 00:11:22,680
don't really fit your persona.

222
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,400
What persona?

223
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:31,361
The elite professional woman

224
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:34,121
who often has light salads
and healthy meals every single day.

225
00:11:34,321 --> 00:11:35,752
Low in fat, filling, and healthy.

226
00:11:36,001 --> 00:11:37,800
You've watched many short videos

227
00:11:37,961 --> 00:11:39,321
with outdated stereotypes.

228
00:11:39,481 --> 00:11:41,040
Career women are also emotional.

229
00:11:41,321 --> 00:11:42,160
Under great pressure,

230
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:44,361
I crave spicy, sweet,
and high-calorie food.

231
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:45,520
It helps lift my mood.

232
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:46,201
That makes sense.

233
00:11:46,721 --> 00:11:48,280
It's never too late for regrets.

234
00:11:49,481 --> 00:11:50,160
But if you

235
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,680
insist on labeling me,

236
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,680
it would be like this.

237
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:55,121
I take immense pride in my career.

238
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:56,721
But I'm not a good mother.

239
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,400
Niuniu will understand
when she grows up.

240
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:02,361
You have no choice.

241
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:04,961
But I still feel guilty.

242
00:12:06,201 --> 00:12:07,121
I love my child deeply.

243
00:12:07,121 --> 00:12:08,361
Yet I also love my work.

244
00:12:09,001 --> 00:12:09,721
What can I do?

245
00:12:09,721 --> 00:12:10,800
24 hours in a day.

246
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:11,441
So I split it,

247
00:12:12,001 --> 00:12:13,721
half for work, and half for my child.

248
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:16,760
But the half for my child
is not sufficient.

249
00:12:17,441 --> 00:12:18,560
Actually, I have no choice.

250
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:21,040
Realistically speaking,

251
00:12:21,961 --> 00:12:23,160
as a single mom,

252
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,121
I have to

253
00:12:25,201 --> 00:12:26,280
handle things alone

254
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,280
and support my family.

255
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,520
Personally,

256
00:12:30,201 --> 00:12:32,680
I feel I can fulfill
my potential and feel a sense

257
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:33,841
of accomplishment at work.

258
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,640
It truly lights me up.

259
00:12:36,481 --> 00:12:37,321
Mothers

260
00:12:37,321 --> 00:12:39,160
always worry about their kids.

261
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:42,201
Every time I leave Niuniu for work,

262
00:12:43,081 --> 00:12:45,040
I'll wrestle with overwhelming guilt

263
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:47,280
for a long time.

264
00:12:49,601 --> 00:12:50,280
Ms. Bai.

265
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,760
You're already doing great.

266
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:55,680
It's incredibly tough
for women to build careers.

267
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,160
I'm luckier than most.

268
00:12:58,721 --> 00:12:59,441
I have

269
00:12:59,441 --> 00:13:00,640
an incredible nanny

270
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:01,680
who's been very helpful.

271
00:13:01,961 --> 00:13:02,760
Even so,

272
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,400
it's been a bumpy road.

273
00:13:06,001 --> 00:13:07,841
Every mother shares the same struggle.

274
00:13:08,321 --> 00:13:10,361
There's always something to worry about.

275
00:13:11,321 --> 00:13:13,520
This is my reality, Tian Min's reality,

276
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,400
and I'm sure your mother's too.

277
00:13:24,841 --> 00:13:26,481
Don't worry. We're here for you.

278
00:13:27,321 --> 00:13:27,920
Okay?

279
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:29,601
We have put our hearts into this.

280
00:13:30,361 --> 00:13:32,001
But why don't we have positive results?

281
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:36,201
But the first verdict
isn't finalized yet.

